title: Density of the population of Finland in 2018 , by region
yAxis: Number of inhabitants per square kilometer
summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Number of inhabitants per square kilometer for 19 number of Finnish Regions.
The Number of inhabitants per square kilometer is appeared to be the highest at Finnish Region Uusimaa and lowest at Finnish Region Lapland.
The highest Finnish Region Uusimaa has 181.8 more Number of inhabitants per square kilometer than the lowest Finnish Region Lapland.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Number of inhabitants per square kilometer for 19 number of Finnish Regions.
Finnish Region Uusimaa has the highest Number of inhabitants per square kilometer and Lapland has the lowest Number of inhabitants per square kilometer.
There is a difference of 181.8 between the maximum Finnish Region Uusimaa and minimum Finnish Region Lapland.
Finnish Region Uusimaa is higher than any other Finnish Regions with value 183.7, followed by Southwest Finland, and Pirkanmaa. Down to Finnish Region Lapland with the lowest value 1.9.
The Finnish Region Lapland has 6.18 times less Number of inhabitants per square kilometer than average.
